INSPECTORÂ General of Police (IGP) Simon Sirro has transferred some officers to improve efficiency in carrying out the duties of the Police Force. Former Police Commander Tarime/Rorya, Assistant Commissioner of Police (ACP) William Mkonda, will take over as Dar es Salaam Special Zone Traffic Officer (ZTO), succeeding ACP Abdi Isango, who will take over as Head of Operation in Mbeya Region. ACP Zuberi Mwombeji, who was former Dar es Salaam Special Zone Chief of Operations, has been transferred to Police Headquarters as Head of Social and Economic Development, being replaced by ACP Kennedy Mgani, who was Mbeya Regional Operations Chief, according to a statement released by Police Spokesperson Senior Assistant Commissioner of Police (SACP) David Misime. SACP Misime further said Dodoma Regional Crime Officer (RCO) ACP Pipi Kayumba moves to Singida Region as Staff Officer One being replaced by Senior Superintendent of Police (SSP) Tarcis Idelfonce, who was the District Police Commander for Dodoma. IGP Sirro has also transferred SSP Jumanne Juke, who was former Geita Officer Commanding District (OCD) to become Rufiji Zonal Crime Officer, replacing ACP Ame Anoqie, who has been transferred to Tarime Rorya as Staff Officer One replacing ACP Geoffrey Sarakikya who becomes the Tarime/Rorya Regional Police Commander.    